article.headline: N. Iowa 79, Bradley 70
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Brooks McKowen and Travis Brown scored 15 points apiece as Northern Iowa beat Bradley 79-70 Tuesday night. Both McKowen and Brown made 3-of-4 from 3-point range. The Panthers (17-12, 8-9 Missouri Valley) shot 8-of-10 as a team from beyond the arc. Daniel Ruffin scored a game-high 20 points and dished out nine assists for Bradley (19-11, 9-8). Bradley led 43-36 at halftime after shooting nearly 52 percent from the field. But during the final 20 minutes, Northern Iowa shot a blistering 77.8 percent while the Braves slumped to 32.1 percent. Eric Coleman scored 14 points and hauled in 10 rebounds, and Grant Stout added 10 points and 10 boards for the Panthers, who outrebounded Bradley 32-22. The Panthers shot 63 percent for the game to Bradley's 41.4 percent. The Braves went 12-for-29 from 3-point range.
